data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0143e5f42edd66b8006998ab745af4819595720e2bfd0ae0b3","logprobs":[],"output_index":2,"sequence_number":509,"text":"Foundry Agent Service is Microsoft’s managed runtime in **Microsoft Foundry** for building and operating **AI agents** end-to-end (dev → deploy → production). It’s aimed at moving beyond “chatbots” to agents that can **orchestrate multi-step work**—like summarizing documents, processing invoices, handling support tickets, or publishing content—while adding the controls needed for enterprise use.【5:0†source】\n\n### What it does\nAt a high level, Foundry Agent Service:\n- **Runs and manages agent conversations** (threads/runs), including multi-turn state and execution flow【5:0†source】\n- **Orchestrates tool calls** (the model decides when to call tools and how to use them)【5:0†source】\n- **Enforces trust & safety controls**, including content safety, plus integration hooks for enterprise policy needs【5:0†source】\n- **Integrates with enterprise platform capabilities** such as identity, networking, and observability so agents can be operated in production settings【5:0†source】\n\n### Tools: how agents get “real capabilities”\nFoundry Agent Service can attach **tools** that let an agent:\n- **Retrieve knowledge** (grounding) from sources like Azure AI Search, file search, Microsoft Fabric, and public web data via Bing-based grounding【5:1†source】\n- **Take actions / automate workflows** via options like Azure Logic Apps, OpenAPI spec integrations, MCP endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, and even browser automation【5:1†source】\n\nThe general flow is: user asks → model infers intent → model optionally calls one or more tools → tool results are used to produce the final answer/action.【5:1†source】\n\n### Web grounding options (example)\nIf you want agents to use current public web info, Foundry supports Bing-based grounding:\n- **Grounding with Bing Search**: broad public web grounding for real-time info【5:3†source】\n- **Grounding with Bing Custom Search (preview)**: restrict web grounding to a **configurable set of domains** you choose【5:2†source】\n\n### Practical takeaway\nIf you’re building something like “an agent that can answer questions *and* file tickets / query internal docs / trigger workflows,” Foundry Agent Service is the piece that provides the **managed agent runtime + tool orchestration + production controls** to operationalize it.【5:0†source】【5:1†source】\n\nIf you tell me whether you’re using the **new** or **classic** Foundry portal/API, I can point you to the right quickstart path and the key concepts (agents, threads, runs, tools) for that specific version."}

